This paper belongs to the field of Natural Language Processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on sentiment analysis. The paper proposes an algorithm for aspect level sentiment analysis, which involves identifying and evaluating opinions about specific aspects of a given topic. This falls under the sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper involves techniques such as dictionary-based methods and tree structures, which are commonly used in Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with managing hostile content over the internet, which falls under the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves the use of algorithms and data structures, which are commonly used in the sub-category of Cybersecurity (cs.CY).
